## Context7 MCP

Before using a new package or adopting a new practice, always query Context7 for up-to-date docs.

### When to use

- Adding a new `npm` dependency — check the current API before writing any code
- Upgrading an existing package — verify breaking changes and new patterns
- Using a framework feature you haven't touched recently (MCP SDK, Zod, etc.)
- Unsure whether a pattern is current or outdated

### How

```
mcp__claude_ai_Context7__resolve-library-id  →  mcp__claude_ai_Context7__query-docs
```

Always resolve the library ID first, then query docs with a specific question.
Don't rely on training data alone — APIs change.
